review_blob: I like the taste of this canned ale better than the Kellys IPA on tap at the brewpub. No real head to speak of, slight medicine odor and palate. Light orange/gold color. I doubt this will get much distribution outside of New Mexico, and this is gonna have a hard time competing with the other packaged IPAs in Albuquerque.
Very spicy. Theres some flavor here Im not very fond of. Possibly clove? Not my cup of cider.
Cloudy and almost white. Very sweet but theres other flavors there that balance it out and make you want to hold it on your tongue for as long as possible.
beer_name: J.K.s Scrumpy Orchard Gate Gold Hard Cider

beer_brewer_name: Crispin Cider Company (Tenth and Blake Beer Co. - MillerCoors)
review_blob: 22 ounce bottle. A really well balanced cider. Not too much sweet, sour or apple.
My first pear cider. Very cloudy. A nice bitter at the beginning that mellows into a fruity sweetness.
beer_name: Fox Barrel Pear Naked Organic Perry

review_blob: Dark (artificial color), dry. More flavor than most ciders. Becomes increasingly sour as you progress.
beer_name: Spire Mountain Dark & Dry Apple Cider

beer_brewer_name: Vermont Hard Cider Company, LLC (C&C; Group)
review_blob: Oh cascade hops, how Ive missed you (since starting me gluten free diet test). Now I can quit eating grapefruit rinds.

Okay NOW were getting somewhere. Spicy, cloudy, delicious, appley. A bit too sweet to drink more than one, but a great starter cider for the evening.  Im tempted to heat it up with some cinnamon sticks and cloves...
beer_name: J.K.s Cuve Winterruption Farmhouse Hard Cider

beer_brewer_name: Magners GB / Shepton Mallet Cider Mill (C&C; Group)
review_blob: Im originally an IPA guy, so I like these ciders that have some flavour and some kick to them. One of the better Ive tried.
Sorry not for me. Bland. Watery. Boring. Not what I expected from something with the word Angry in the name.

beer_brewer_name: Vermont Hard Cider Company, LLC (C&C; Group)
review_blob: Nothing spectacular here, just a middle of the road easily drinkable cider. Available in 12 pack bottles or cans and it will do in a pinch.
568 mL bottle from Total Wine (which opened not too long ago so this hasnt been sitting around forever). Some bitter and aftertaste, and I like it. Best cider Ive tried so far.
Not the worst gluten free ale Ive tried. Itll do in a bind. Rather flat and too sweet.
I just wish this alcohol content wasnt so high so I could drink it constantly.  This may be the best brew Ive ever tasted.    I cant imagine what this must taste like on tap.
UPDATED: OCT 2, 2011
Bomber from Barons.  No head.  Lovely colour.  A strong IPA.  Very dry.  I will sip this the rest of the evening until I pass out.
Bomber from Barons.  Oh my...  This is everything an IPA should be.  Bitter.  Dry.  Bitter.  And Dry.  90 IBUs.
22oz bomber from Barons.  Heady and lacy.  A tad bit foul odor, but the taste is good.  Sweet and dry.  Would love to try this on draft.

I had this on draft at the Blues and Brews fest 2011, and it may possibly have been the best ale I have ever tasted.  I managed to get a bottle version recently, and while not as good as that draft, its still a great ale.  Deep color, not much head.  Fantastic aroma, almost overpowering. A very sweet start that quickly fades to a dryness, without being bitter at all.  Well done.

Holy cow Im eating hops.  Literally.  Let this sucker sit for a few minutes to let them settle.  Sip sip sip.  Slow.  Damn this is good.  Very interesting hop aroma,,, a nice change of pace from cascade for an IPA.  A great novelty ale.

I love this ale.  Sweet aroma and taste, but not overpowering, just enough to force me to sip it instead of gulp.   The flavor tells me this is not 8% but my belly is telling me yes it is.  Maybe I can get some sleep now...
Stinky.  First sip is a punch in the face.  Pucker up.  But everyone is spot on this is really good towards the end of that bomber, I wish I had more.

I normally dont mind wheat beers, but this ones got a sour, pungent bite that lingers, making the next sips harder and harder to take.  It helps if you hold your breath and let the beer slide just down the center of your tongue.   Sorry, not my style of brew.  I received a crateful of random brews for X-mas and Im gonna slog through then all.

My 100th beer rating turns out to be a local brew made within 1 mile of me.  How awesome is that?  One of my favorite IPAs right now, maybe cause its always a bit cheaper than the stuff they have to truck in.
Really dry and hoppy.  Almost too much.

At first sip I thought maybe I wouldnt be able to drink this.  Way too over the top was my first impression .  But the finish on this brew is just fantastic.  Flavour is your typical heavy dark chocolate stout, and once your mouth gets over that initial shock, the rest is pure heaven.  I was sad when the bottle was gone.
Is pretty tasty... bitter, but not over the top.  Good to see Sierra taking some pride in the process again.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Harvest Wet Hop IPA - Northern Hemisphere

review_blob: Wow.  Just wow.  I just want to sit and inhale the beer.  It smells like it was just brewed today.  The flavor and balance are perfect.  Theres something different... what is that?  Fantastic beer.  Buying a case tomorrow.
beer_name: Stone Sublimely Self Righteous Black IPA

review_blob: Thats a good IPA.  Better than their regular pale ale.  This one has a definite bite to it.  Great looking head.  On draft at Old Pecos Trail grill.
On draft at the brewery - Delicious brew.  Nicely balanced in all areas.  I could drink this one every day.
Sample draft from the brewery - quite interesting.  From Shorts other brews youd expect a lot of chocolate in this, but this ones quite subtle.
Looks like a cider, smells like a fireplace. Initially quite disgusting, but after a few sips it kind of grows on ya.  And when they say "Smoked" they mean it.
Is it possible to overdo it?  Yes.  But its still a good thing.  Not an ale I want to drink everyday, but fun.  This thing is brutal.
Its very hard not to give this a perfect score.  Quite possibly the perfect example of what I expect from an IPA.

A decent beer from Red Hook?  Havent had one of those for a few years!  Nothing great about this beer, it looks like lager,  smells like a macro, but the hops save it from the bin.  Truly the only thing worth buying from my local SuperGroceryMart... cheap too.
Not a bad bottle of beer for something all the way from Maine.  A sweet pale ale, with definite astringent, but goes away quick.  A good changeup from overhopped IPAs.
beer_name: Sea Dog (Old East) India Pale Ale

review_blob: Malty.  Really nice color for a brown.  Nothing spectacular, but very drinkable.

Very surprised.  I expected a watered down  ale for ballpark fans of the Simpsons.  Medium body on this, very slight bitter.  Nice mouthfeel, and a very balanced taste.  Nothing overwhelming in any direction.  A great ale to chug at the stadium when everyone else is sipping their Miller Lights.
Has the stench of lager, but not the normal lager taste.  Sweet and unassuming.  A very easy beer to drink.  If there was no such thing as ale this would probably be my choice of brews.

I popped the top and the cap almost exploded off.  Malty malty aroma,  good head, nice lacing.  A dark beer but still has a very pretty amber color.  I cant believe this is up at 9%, the alcohol does not overpower the ale at all.  Good Show Avery!

beer_brewer_name: Socorro Springs Brewing (no longer brewing - see Eddyline)
review_blob: From growler purchased at the brewery. Gold.  Light headed.  Piney soapy.  This is not the draft I had at the restaurant.  That ESB was really good.  This one not so much.  The food at the restaurant is really good too btw,  I highly suggest stopping there on any road trips through Socorro.
Pilsner stench.  Burning aftertaste.  This sixer might have been skunked for all I know.  Theres nothing "ale" about this.

A quite interesting ale.  Hoppy, but Im not sure at all what type.  A bit of sour.  Long lingering subtle bitter.   Picture a fuller, heavier Bass.  Not something Id drink everyday, but a great change up when Im bored with my everyday favorites.
Imperial IPA... Yum yum. Hops galore when the bottle is first opened, but the aroma quickly disipates.  Much hop flavour, but not too bitter.  Very clear, light red.
Like biting into a grapefruit.  Good for a change of pace.  Makes you hum Doors songs while you drink it.

Smells terrible.  No head.  Almost no color.  A good amount of fizzy hides some of the flavor, and then its gone before you can taste too much of it.  So, no harm, no foul I guess.  Just hold your nose when you drink.
I love this beer.  One problem.  Its 11%.  The bottle I got poured with a perfect, dark brown head.  I expected this beer to be completely overpowering but it really is well balanced.
beer_name: Beer Valley Black Flag Imperial Stout

review_blob: UPDATED: JUL 23, 2007
Beautiful color and head.  Smooth body.   Slight stink.  A very mellow delicous beer.  I cant get over how creamy the head is.
12 oz aluminum can.  A pale lager indeed.  But a heck of a lot better than most canned lagers.  Has that cheap lager aftertaste that I cant stand though.
My favourite beer right now.  Rich, full bodied.  Good flavour and palette that are not too overpowering.  Above average alchohol content.  And easily recycled can!
